------------------------------------------------------

increasing the temperature T, at fixed n. of particles, the max time step allowed decreases (due to thermal noise) and the ratio std/mean increases;
increasing the n. of particles at a certain T, the max time step allowed increases reaching a plateau;


T=1
N=1 dt=0.006-0.007
N=2 dt=0.025-0.03
N=3 dt=0.025-0.03
N=10 dt=0.03

T=10
N=1 dt=0.002-0.0025
N=2 dt=0.007-0.008
N=3 dt=0.007-0.008
N=5 dt=0.007-0.008
